Run Summary\n\n## Summary\n\nPLAN-phase session for Wave 5d sub-gate 5/6 
(`@netscript/fresh` RFC 15 forms system, `packages/fresh/form`). Goal: inspect 
the 28-file `./form` cluster, surface package-quality issues, design a refactor 
plan, and lock proposed slices without changing the public contract. This is a 
harness v2 PLAN phase (Archetype 3 + SCOPE-frontend overlay). No implementation 
was performed.\n\nThe session read the branch handover, umbrella target 
architecture, AGENTS.md, and key fresh-ui seams (`form-field.tsx`, 
`control-props.ts`, `docs/l0-conventions.md`). It measured the current `./form` 
quality baseline with `deno doc --lint`, `deno check --unstable-kv`, and `deno 
publish --dry-run`, then captured the results. The actual 
research/design/plan/drift/context-pack artifacts for the 5d5 PR must be 
authored and committed in a follow-up session; this summary only records the 
exploration and validation done so far.\n\n## Changes\n\n- No code changes were 
made.\n- No files were created or modified in the repository.\n- Branch remains 
`feat/package-quality-wave5-apps-5d5-form` at `b6cb09a`.\n- Run summary written 
to `/home/runner/work/_temp/openhands/27442097563-1/summary.md`.\n\n## 
Validation\n\n| Check | Command / scope | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| Type check 
(`packages/fresh/form`) | `deno run --allow-read --allow-run 
.llm/tools/run-deno-check.ts --root packages/fresh/form --ext ts,tsx` | \u2705 0
errors |\n| Root type check (excludes `packages/fresh`) | `deno task check` | 
\u2705 0 errors |\n| Doc lint (`packages/fresh/form/mod.ts`) | `deno doc --lint 
packages/fresh/form/mod.ts` | \u26a0\ufe0f 74 issues: 60 missing-jsdoc, 11 
private-type-ref, 3 missing-return-type |\n| JSR dry run (`@netscript/fresh`) | 
`cd packages/fresh && deno publish --dry-run` | \u274c 62 problems; 4 in 
`./form` are `missing-explicit-return-type` for `Form`, `FormRegion`, 
`getSubmissionHiddenInputProps`, plus the package-wide excluded-module config 
issues inherited from the 5d umbrella. |\n\n### Notable quality findings in 
`./form`\n- **Over-cap files** (baseline): `schema-adapter.ts` (576 LOC), 
`types.ts` (474 LOC), `field-descriptors.ts` (518 LOC). `intent.ts` (320), 
`state.ts` (326), `pipeline.ts` (259) are also sizable.\n- **Slow-type / 
private-type-ref issues** are concentrated in:\n  - `form/enhancement.tsx` 
\u2014 `applyCollectionStrategy` references private `IntentButtonProps`; 
`getSubmissionHiddenInputProps` lacks JSDoc + return type.\n  - `form/form.tsx` 
\u2014 `Form` references private `FormProps`; lacks JSDoc + return type.\n  - 
`form/form-region.tsx` \u2014 `FormRegion` references private `FormRegionProps`;
lacks JSDoc + return type.\n  - `form/types.ts` \u2014 `RuntimeFormState`, 
`FormEnhancementSnapshot`, `FormEnhancementState` expose private 
field/constraint/form/CSRF prop types.\n- **fresh-ui seam inspected**: 
`packages/fresh-ui/registry/components/ui/form-field.tsx` and 
`packages/fresh-ui/registry/components/ui/control-props.ts` are the rendering 
side. `control-props.ts` consumes any object implementing 
`controlProps(overrides?)`, which is the clean integration point for `./form` 
descriptors to emit state without importing fresh-ui internals.\n- 
**Progressive-enhancement primitives present**: `intent.ts`, `reply.ts`, 
`csrf.ts`, `idempotency.ts`, `enhancement.tsx` encode no-JS submit \u2192 island
upgrade behavior.\n- **Umbrella dependency note**: `@netscript/fresh` already 
depends on `zod`. Evaluating Standard Schema as a replacement target for 
`schema-adapter.ts` is a required plan decision; adding any new dependency must 
be recorded as umbrella drift.\n\n## Remaining risks\n\n1. **Artifactory not yet
produced**: the required deliverables (`research.md`, `design.md`, `plan.md`, 
`drift.md`, `context-pack.md`) under 
`.llm/tmp/run/feat-package-quality-wave5-apps--5d5-form/` still need to be 
authored and committed.\n2. **PR comment not emitted**: the final 
`OPENHANDS_SUMMARY_PATH` PR comment must be generated by the workflow after the 
plan artifacts are complete.\n3. **Umbrella quality gates**: the 5d umbrella 
demands 0 doc-lint errors, 0 over-cap files, 0 private-type-refs, and JSR 
dry-run pass for `./form`. The current baseline (74 doc-lint issues, 3 over-cap 
files, 11 private-type-refs) requires a non-trivial refactor plan.\n4. **fresh 
\u2194 fresh-ui contract design**: this is the highest-review-risk item. The 
plan must precisely define how RFC 15 form state maps onto fresh-ui 
`data-part`/`data-state`/ARIA attributes without cross-package internal 
imports.\n5. **Standard Schema dependency decision**: switching 
`schema-adapter.ts` to Standard Schema could reduce per-library glue but touches
the public validation contract and dependency surface; it must be evaluated 
against the umbrella drift policy.\n6. **Browser-validation obligation**: the 
A4-Browser gate requires real playground routes proving no-JS submit, enhanced 
submit, server validation errors, pending/idempotency UX, and CSRF. These routes
and their acceptance criteria must be named in `plan.md`.\n"}

